# README-First Workflow

- Before updating `README.md`, always read the current file first.
- Keep `README.md` aligned with the actual code structure and runtime behavior.
- When new features or refactors are introduced, update `README.md` only after the code changes are complete.
- Prefer concise, developer-focused notes: setup, architecture, key files, and data flow.
